So here's what -- I won't tell
you that because I want you

00:22:55.750 --> 00:22:57.640
to read it and I want
it to feel fresh to you.

00:22:57.640 --> 00:23:02.300
But what I will say is, every
question will be answered.

00:23:02.300 --> 00:23:04.220
All the questions
will be answered.

00:23:04.220 --> 00:23:06.330
And Lu is a very
different kind of character,

00:23:06.330 --> 00:23:09.090
and that's all I'm going to say.

00:23:09.090 --> 00:23:12.900
And thank you for reading the
other three, I appreciate that.

00:23:12.900 --> 00:23:17.320
&gt;&gt; Okay. &gt; I've read -- I
started reading your books

00:23:17.320 --> 00:23:21.150
in like seventh grade, and I've
been following them since then.

00:23:21.150 --> 00:23:23.700
And I feel like I've watched
you grow in popularity as I go

00:23:23.700 --> 00:23:25.070
to each of the events you're at.

00:23:25.070 --> 00:23:26.560
And like your books are too.

00:23:26.560 --> 00:23:29.580
Like I think Long Way Down
is becoming a play, right?

00:23:29.580 --> 00:23:30.880
&gt;&gt; Jason Reynolds:
Yeah, for sure.

00:23:30.880 --> 00:23:32.570
&gt;&gt; Like how are you responding
to that, dealing with it?

00:23:32.570 --> 00:23:33.870
&gt;&gt; Jason Reynolds:
To the success?

00:23:33.870 --> 00:23:35.170
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:23:35.170 --> 00:23:36.470
&gt;&gt; Jason Reynolds: That's
a very good question.

00:23:36.470 --> 00:23:37.940
So my best friend
is here, right,

00:23:37.940 --> 00:23:39.260
my best friend in the world.

00:23:39.260 --> 00:23:41.060
Somebody that I've
known since I was --

00:23:41.060 --> 00:23:44.540
it's been 31 years of
friendship with this person.

00:23:44.540 --> 00:23:46.870
And he's in the crowd.

00:23:46.870 --> 00:23:49.970
And people like him are
sort of the anchors --

00:23:49.970 --> 00:23:53.300
like things get crazy and they
get noisy, and it's easy for me

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:54.600
to look out into the audience --

00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:55.990
and I'm so grateful for
all of you who have come.

00:23:55.990 --> 00:23:57.890
And I'm so fortunate that
any of you care anything

00:23:57.890 --> 00:23:59.530
about the things
that I've written.

00:23:59.530 --> 00:24:01.940
But this isn't my
real life, right.

00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:04.190
Like this is a part of my life
and it's a part that I love

00:24:04.190 --> 00:24:05.490
and I'm sharing it with you.

00:24:05.490 --> 00:24:08.370
But my real life is at
my mom's kitchen table.

00:24:08.370 --> 00:24:11.090
My real life is with my home
boys who've known me my whole

00:24:11.090 --> 00:24:13.860
life and know all the things
that y'all will never know.

00:24:13.860 --> 00:24:16.980
Right. And so I try my
best to surround myself

00:24:16.980 --> 00:24:20.210
with like the people who
love me and who know me.

00:24:20.210 --> 00:24:21.510
Because they're the
ones who are going

00:24:21.510 --> 00:24:22.810
to always tell me the truth.

00:24:22.810 --> 00:24:25.650
And we all need the truth, even
when it makes us uncomfortable.

00:24:25.650 --> 00:24:27.450
And that's how I deal
with it, you know.

00:24:27.450 --> 00:24:31.090
[applause].

00:24:31.090 --> 00:24:32.780
You got to wait till the end.

00:24:32.780 --> 00:24:34.080
I got you the very
last question,

00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:35.980
but I can't get you right now.

00:24:35.980 --> 00:24:37.280
Yeah?

00:24:37.280 --> 00:24:39.290
&gt;&gt; Hi. So I really admire
your craft because you try

00:24:39.290 --> 00:24:40.590
so many different things.

00:24:40.590 --> 00:24:45.970
You've done a verse novel
that took place like in a day.

00:24:45.970 --> 00:24:49.210
You're on to four
of the Track books

00:24:49.210 --> 00:24:53.260
and then you've done a
Spiderman book that is based

00:24:53.260 --> 00:24:55.290
on a character that we love.

00:24:55.290 --> 00:25:00.550
So what is your craft
process like?

00:25:00.550 --> 00:25:02.730
Or maybe I'm mostly
just thinking

00:25:02.730 --> 00:25:05.670
of who is the hardest
character you've ever written?

00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:07.390
&gt;&gt; Jason Reynolds: So first
of all, I want to thank you

00:25:07.390 --> 00:25:10.770
because I do these talks and
I do panels all the time,

00:25:10.770 --> 00:25:12.670
and you know what people
never ask me about?

00:25:12.670 --> 00:25:14.870
Craft. Ever.

00:25:14.870 --> 00:25:17.780
People want to know whatever
it is they think I represent.

00:25:17.780 --> 00:25:19.690
But I work as hard as
everybody else in this business.

00:25:19.690 --> 00:25:22.580
I sit down at the page and
-- you know what I mean?

00:25:22.580 --> 00:25:23.880
Like for me it's craft, right.

00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:25.850
[inaudible] So thank
you for that, right.

00:25:25.850 --> 00:25:28.600
And so in terms of the hardest
character I've written --

00:25:28.600 --> 00:25:31.830
oh, it's hard.

00:25:31.830 --> 00:25:33.130
That's a tough question.

00:25:33.130 --> 00:25:34.430
I mean, there's so
many different --

00:25:34.430 --> 00:25:38.270
I mean, Patina was not a
difficult character to write,

00:25:38.270 --> 00:25:40.260
but she was one that I wanted
to take really, really,

00:25:40.260 --> 00:25:42.930
really good care of and to
think about and be thoughtful

00:25:42.930 --> 00:25:44.260
about how to write her.

00:25:44.260 --> 00:25:46.680
Because I didn't want --

00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:50.580
I wanted to write a girl
character as a human being.

00:25:50.580 --> 00:25:53.950
And that took time
and compassion,

00:25:53.950 --> 00:25:55.980
me dealing with my own stuff.

00:25:55.980 --> 00:25:58.250
Me really sort of like
taking my time to make sure

00:25:58.250 --> 00:26:00.700
that I nailed this down, that
I'm not swaying too far this way

00:26:00.700 --> 00:26:03.640
or that way, slipping into
all the cliches that so many

00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:07.720
of us slip into and
really writing a young lady

00:26:07.720 --> 00:26:11.380
as a human being dealing with
all the things that young ladies

00:26:11.380 --> 00:26:12.680
that I grew up with deal with.

00:26:12.680 --> 00:26:15.500
And so that was probably
not the hardest character,

00:26:15.500 --> 00:26:17.800
but the character that
was most challenging.

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:19.190
Thank you for that.

